<head>
  <meta name="title" content="Chamber Two (Furlongs Room) (Samwel)"/>
  <meta name="description" content="Chamber Two (Furlongs Room) is a named lower-level space in Furlongs plan (Feranec et al. 2007 Fig. 2), reached only by a deep drop requiring climbing gear, and an excavated chamber sharing Chamber Ones stratigraphy (deepest dig 2.5 m). By "/>
  <meta name="rights" content="Interpretive: Room size and shape, the deep floor depth, identifying the documented deep drop AS the maidens ~90 ft hole (modeled as one shaft), the exact pit geometry, speleothems, breakdown, pool placement, light"/>
</head>
